libsais
------------------------------------------
The libsais provides simple C99 API to construct suffix array and
Burrows-Wheeler transformed string from a given string over constant-size
alphabet. The algorithm runs in a linear time using typically only ~16KB of
extra memory (with 2n bytes as absolute worst-case; where n is the length of
the string). OpenMP acceleration uses 200KB of addition memory per thread.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  libgomp1-13.4.0-1
  libsais-devel-2.10.4-1bl1
  libsais2-2.10.4-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/IlyaGrebnov/libsais

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/IlyaGrebnov/libsais/archive/refs/tags/v2.10.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libsais-2.10.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libsais-2.10.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libsais-2.10.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsais-2.10.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsais2-2.10.4-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libsais-devel-2.10.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libsais)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libsais.README
  /usr/share/doc/libsais/Benchmarks.md
  /usr/share/doc/libsais/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/libsais/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libsais/README.md

(libsais2)
  /usr/bin/cygsais-2.dll

(libsais-devel)
  /usr/include/libsais.h
  /usr/include/libsais16.h
  /usr/include/libsais16x64.h
  /usr/include/libsais64.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/libsais/libsaisConfig-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/libsais/libsaisConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/libsais/libsaisConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/libsais.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libsais.pc

